      {
        "id": 264652,
        "name": "",
        "username": "Toldry",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/toldry/{size}/51482_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-28T15:13:16.522Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Went I wanted to link my Signal Android to my Signal for Desktop, I did the following steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Open Signal Desktop</li>\n<li>It tells me to scan a QR code to link my device</li>\n</ol>\n<p>So I let my intuition guide me, and I opened my Signal Android, and:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Touch the three-dots menu on the top-left</li>\n<li>Select “Settings”</li>\n<li>I saw a button with QR logo on the right (see screenshot):</li>\n</ol>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/9/7/97a0e30e3cbd9383762723dd1022fb5656fbfe56.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/97a0e30e3cbd9383762723dd1022fb5656fbfe56\" title=\"image.psd\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/9/7/97a0e30e3cbd9383762723dd1022fb5656fbfe56_2_225x500.jpeg\" alt=\"image.psd\" data-base62-sha1=\"lDmNoxVBcNibPLaaDB1gSc4skvA\" width=\"225\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/9/7/97a0e30e3cbd9383762723dd1022fb5656fbfe56_2_225x500.jpeg, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/9/7/97a0e30e3cbd9383762723dd1022fb5656fbfe56_2_337x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/9/7/97a0e30e3cbd9383762723dd1022fb5656fbfe56_2_450x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"202225\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image.psd</span><span class=\"informations\">576×1280 54.5 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<ol start=\"6\">\n<li>I touched the QR button and was greeted with this screen:</li>\n</ol>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/7/a/7adbc9a30994f089b0b044d6ba778dd826bee9e1.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/7adbc9a30994f089b0b044d6ba778dd826bee9e1\" title=\"image.psd(1)\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/a/7adbc9a30994f089b0b044d6ba778dd826bee9e1_2_225x500.jpeg\" alt=\"image.psd(1)\" data-base62-sha1=\"hwR8WuTjqrLoaQtvu8yE9boxstj\" width=\"225\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/a/7adbc9a30994f089b0b044d6ba778dd826bee9e1_2_225x500.jpeg, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/a/7adbc9a30994f089b0b044d6ba778dd826bee9e1_2_337x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/a/7adbc9a30994f089b0b044d6ba778dd826bee9e1_2_450x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"3B425A\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image.psd(1)</span><span class=\"informations\">576×1280 113 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<ol start=\"7\">\n<li>I touched the “Scan” button</li>\n<li>Scanned the QR code on my Signal for Desktop</li>\n<li>Was greeted with this uninformative error screen:</li>\n</ol>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/b/5/b5cded78f541f112a63444686c08008fa947540c.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/b5cded78f541f112a63444686c08008fa947540c\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/b/5/b5cded78f541f112a63444686c08008fa947540c_2_225x500.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"pWjCruZd0uqiErtCRq9IUnXFaXi\" width=\"225\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/b/5/b5cded78f541f112a63444686c08008fa947540c_2_225x500.jpeg, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/b/5/b5cded78f541f112a63444686c08008fa947540c_2_337x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/b/5/b5cded78f541f112a63444686c08008fa947540c_2_450x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"343432\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">576×1280 63.2 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>It took a lot of frustrating fiddling around (and zero results on Google) until I finally understood that this QR-scanning screen in Signal Android is only for scanning contacts, and not for linking devices.</p>\n<p>In order to link a device, I needed to do:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Settings</li>\n<li>Linked devices</li>\n<li>Link a new device</li>\n</ol>\n<p>My suggestion is: when the user tried to scan a contact QR, and Signal identifies that this is a device-linking QR, then show a more informative error message, such as:<br>\n“This QR code is for linking a new device, and not for adding a contact. Do you want to link to this device? [Yes] [Cancel]”</p>",
