        "id": 264661,
        "name": "Wyatt Childers",
        "username": "Dark_Arc",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/53a042/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-28T16:35:29.784Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I’m not sure streamlining this would be in Signal’s best interest.</p>\n<p>There’s currently phishing campaigns abusing the linked devices feature. Adding more ways to accidentally link a device (granted, you’d have to not read, but plenty of people just click/tap things because they’re used to nuisance popups) might not be great.</p>\n<p>EDIT: Maybe if they implemented this first <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/device-linking-phishing/68076\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Device Linking Phishing</a></p>",
